Subject:    resolver question
From:       <a href="?a=95837693400017&r=1&w=2">Greg Satz &lt;SATZ () SU-SIERRA ! ARPA&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198509">1985-09-12 8:23:41</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426536&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426536&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I want to write a program that uses the Berkeley resolver. It just takes
a host name and returns all known host addresses and names (including
nicknames).  With the host table it was just a (quick?) lookup. With
domains it seems a little more complex. I notice in the RFC that I can
ask for all RRs for a given host. However, it doesn't seem to return any
CNAME RRs which would tell me the aliases for that host. The question(s)
become:

1) How do I get CNAME RRs from a server for a particular host?

or

2) Is there another way of getting a hosts addresses and nicknames?

Please reply to me directly as I am not on this list.
